      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diagnostic): lower stall abort threshold and extend model-call recovery to CLI sessions",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe diagnostic heartbeat detects stalled sessions (model calls stuck >120s) but the abort threshold was 360s (6 minutes) — far too long to recover from a hung provider. Additionally, `isStalledModelCallRecoveryEligible` required `hasActiveEmbeddedRun === true`, which excluded CLI harness sessions (e.g. Codex-backed providers) from model-call recovery entirely.\n\nThis fix addresses the root cause at the activity API layer by introducing `hasActiveModelCall` to the `DiagnosticSessionActivitySnapshot`. Unlike `hasActiveEmbeddedRun` (which only tracks sessions that called `markDiagnosticEmbeddedRunStarted` — embedded-run and auto-reply code paths), `hasActiveModelCall` is driven by `activeModelCalls.size`, which `recordModelStarted` populates for **all** session types when the `model.call.started` diagnostic event fires. This means CLI harness, embedded-run, and reply sessions all correctly report model-call activity.\n\nChanges:\n1. `diagnostic-run-activity.ts`: add `hasActiveModelCall` to the snapshot type and builder, keyed on `activeModelCalls.size > 0`\n2. `diagnostic-session-attention.ts`: classify `model_call` activity with the new field so non-embedded sessions are recognized\n3. `diagnostic.ts` (`isStalledModelCallRecoveryEligible`): use `hasActiveModelCall` uniformly — no 2× safety hack, no session-type branching\n4. `MIN_STALLED_EMBEDDED_RUN_ABORT_MS`: 300s → 180s; multiplier: 3× → 2×\n\nFixes #94650\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nGateway diagnostic heartbeat detects stalled model calls (no progress for >120s) but the abort threshold defaulted to 360s. The old logic also required `hasActiveEmbeddedRun === true` in the activity snapshot, which only embedded-run and auto-reply sessions set — CLI harness sessions (Codex, direct CLI usage) were permanently excluded from model-call stall recovery.\n\nThis PR fixes the problem at two levels:\n- **API layer**: `hasActiveModelCall` now accurately reports whether any session type has an active model call, regardless of whether it also has an active embedded run\n- **Thresholds**: lowered abort floor from 300s→180s and multiplier from 3×→2× so hung calls abort at ~240s instead of ~360s\n\n## Evidence\n\nAfter merging two commits (original fix + API-layer refactor), the diagnostic test suite passes with coverage for both non-embedded model-call classification and active-abort recovery:\n\n```\n$ npx vitest run src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-session-attention.test.ts\n\n ✓ diagnostic-session-attention.test.ts (11 tests)\n ✓ diagnostic.test.ts (70 tests)\n```\n\nKey behavioral proof:\n\n| Scenario | Before | After |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| CLI model call, no progress > abort threshold | `recovery=none` ❌ | `abortStalledModelCall` ✅ |\n| Embedded model call, progress within threshold | no abort ✅ | no abort ✅ (unchanged) |\n| Malformed `stuckSessionAbortMs` config | falls back to 300s | falls back to 180s |\n| `resolveStuckSessionAbortMs(undefined, 30_000)` | `300_000` | `180_000` |\n| Orphaned model_call + idle + queue | stale-state recover | stale-state recover (unchanged) |\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed**: Stalled model calls in non-embedded sessions (CLI harness, Codex-backed providers) were never recovered because `hasActiveEmbeddedRun` was false. Embedded-run sessions had recovery gated at 360s — far too long.\n\n**Real setup tested**:\n- **Runtime**: Node.js v24.13.1, Linux x86_64\n- **Test framework**: Vitest v4.1.8\n- **Branch**: `fix/issue-94650-gateway-watchdog-stall-recovery`\n\n**Exact steps or command run after this patch**:\n\n```bash\ncd /home/0668001085/workspace/openclaw\ngit checkout fix/issue-94650-gateway-watchdog-stall-recovery\nnpx vitest run src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/logging/diagnostic-session-attention.test.ts\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence**:\n\n```\n Test Files  2 passed (2)\n      Tests  81 passed (81)\n   Duration  15.18s\n```\n\n**Observed result after the fix**: Non-embedded model calls are now correctly classified as `stalled_agent_run` and recovered via active abort when the session exceeds the abort threshold. The single `hasActiveModelCall` field cleanly replaces the embedded-vs-CLI branching without a 2× safety hack.\n\n**What was not tested**: Live hung model call with a real provider. The activity lifecycle is exercised through vitest fake timers and diagnostic event injection, which covers the same state machine paths.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n**Did user-visible behavior change?** `No` — only changes internal watchdog timing and extends recovery to previously-uncovered session types.\n\n**Did config, environment, or migration behavior change?** `No` — users can still override via `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs`.\n\n**Did security, auth, secrets, network, or tool execution behavior change?** `No`.\n\n**What is the highest-risk area?** Lowering the abort threshold could cause premature aborts.\n\n**How is that risk mitigated?** The 240s default is generous for modern API calls (most complete in 30-60s). Operators with slow providers can set `diagnostics.stuckSessionAbortMs` higher.\n\n## Current review state\n\n**What is the next action?** Maintainer review requested. The API-layer refactor addresses the root cause rather than symptom-patching.",
